OL,3,CSir Frank Atherton accepts his face
OL,4,Ccoverings advice 'weakened public
OL,5,Cmessaging'
OL,7,FSecondly, he thought wearing of face
OL,8,Fcoverings would promote "risky
OL,9,Fbehaviours" and thirdly his concern
OL,10,Fwas that the face coverings being used
OL,11,Fgenerally in the UK did not meet World
OL,12,FHealth Organisation standards, and
OL,13,Ftherefore would have little material
OL,14,Fimpact on reducing the spread of the
OL,15,Fvirus.
OL,17,FThe inquiry was shown a page of Sir
OL,18,FFrank's notepad from 7 June 2020 in
OL,19,Fwhich he wrote "Is there sufficient
OL,20,Fevidence to support mandatory use?"
