OL,7,F"It became confusing to the public
OL,8,Fthat we were not aligned and that we
OL,9,Fwere doing slightly different on face
OL,10,Fcoverings so it was me trying to make
OL,11,Fsure that ministers understood that
OL,12,Fthis was their decision.
OL,14,F"But my advice was that the evidence
OL,15,F(for mandating face coverings) was not
OL,16,Frobust."
OL,18,FAsked by the Counsel to the Inquiry,
OL,19,F"Do you think taking this stance
OL,20,Fweakened public messaging?
