OL,7,FAsked by Kirsten Heaven KC how he
OL,8,Fsatisfied himself that vulnerable
OL,9,Fpeople in care homes were going to be
OL,10,Fprotected, Sir Frank said the numbers
OL,11,Fof people leaving hospital for care
OL,12,Fhomes were "not large numbers" and
OL,13,Fthere was "no safer alternative" to
OL,14,Fthe policy.
OL,16,F"The common view was that care homes
OL,17,Fought to be able to manage cases of
OL,18,Finfectious disease by isolating people
OL,19,Fwithin there," he said.
